7,0.18804578,-0.02527809,0.00340963,-0.00848134,0.01437178,-0.03275249,0.12254114,0.03872105,0.05320456,-0.01661556,0.13237388,0.01950462,0.02938412,-0.04447646,-0.00780114,-0.08188765,-0.03357987,0.04587118,-0.04870168,0.04920198,-0.01629485,0.02067781,0.06505844,-0.01700358,-0.04075650,-0.05749162,-0.03905646,-0.03727280,0.04311780,-0.02697573,0.01269897,0.00384976,-0.03163422,-0.02175402,0.00433226,-0.04357137,-0.08208991,0.04529231,0.05539721,-0.02729447,0.06732544,-0.01010425,0.00397713]',E'Request scope\n\nWhen using annotation-driven components or Java configuration, the `@RequestScope` annotation\ncan be used to assign a component to the `request` scope. The following example shows how\nto do so:\n\n[tabs]\n======\nJava::\n+\n[source,java,indent=0,subs="verbatim,quotes"]\n----\n	@RequestScope\n	@Component\n	public class LoginAction {\n		// ...\n	}\n----\n\nKotlin::\n+\n[source,kotlin,indent=0,subs="verbatim,quotes"]\n----\n	@RequestScope\n	@Component\n	class LoginAction {\n		// ...\n	}\n----\n======','{"source": "spring-framework", "version": "7", "language": "java", "title": "Factory Scopes.Adoc", "section_title": "factory-scopes.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/main/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc", "topics": "spring,framework,factory,scopes.adoc", "categories": "java,enterprise,ioc,web"}');
