,0.04533894,-0.02775304,0.03830504,0.07618878,0.00328585,0.02655118,0.04018877,0.01930325,0.00539501,0.14890814,-0.00283879,0.01005843,-0.04580355,0.00162249,-0.05142073,0.04653060,0.04456747,-0.09283524,0.01298577,0.02400965,-0.04643833,0.02627063,-0.02057662,-0.00585326,-0.01317865,-0.05405810,-0.00503214,-0.01837561,-0.02599962,0.01994432,-0.03065138,0.01800011,-0.01288757,-0.00732439,-0.01126436,-0.06499831,0.03268060,0.00864623,0.04365537,0.01379108,-0.00064950,-0.01882024]',E'Scoped Beans as Dependencies\n\nThus, you need the following (correct and complete) configuration when injecting\n`request-` and `session-scoped` beans into collaborating objects, as the following example\nshows:\n\n[source,xml,indent=0,subs="verbatim,quotes"]\n----\n	<bean id="userPreferences" class="com.something.UserPreferences" scope="session">\n		<aop:scoped-proxy/>\n	</bean>\n\n	<bean id="userManager" class="com.something.UserManager">\n		<property name="userPreferences" ref="userPreferences"/>\n	</bean>\n----','{"source": "spring-framework", "version": "7", "language": "java", "title": "Factory Scopes.Adoc", "section_title": "factory-scopes.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/main/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/beans/factory-scopes.adoc", "topics": "spring,framework,factory,scopes.adoc", "categories": "java,enterprise,ioc,web"}');
